 " }{TEXT 259 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for
 finding the coefficients of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^
n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 
267 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is relatively obvious that the coefficie
nt of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*b^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!
\"\"F()%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  for any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" 
}{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by
 the number of ways we can choose " }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of \+
the " }{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }
{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }
{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The numbe
r of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosin
g " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 " at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" 
"6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is given by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "
nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kG
F*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
