0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "2.  Pascal's \+
Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use Maple to \+
construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick will be t
o get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Maple comma
nd for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(expression(
i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with index i and m.
.n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}
