" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "5.  Solving Systems of Equations in Sever
al Variables.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 49 "When we have an equation in two variables, e.g.  " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x -2*y = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"y
GF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 147 "  we often associate with it a graph, th
e set of points (x,y) in the two-dimensional plane which satisfy the e
quation.  For a linear equation like " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x-2*y = 5" "6
#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 89 " t
he graph is a straight line.  For more a complicated equation in two v
ariables, e.g.,  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "2*x^3 -3*x + y^2 = x*y" "6#/,(*&\"
\"#\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$F'F'*&F*F'F)F'!\"\"*$%\"yGF&F'*&F)F'F.F'" }{TEXT 
-1 45 "  the graph becomes a more complicated curve." }}{PARA 8 "" 1 "
" {TEXT -1 25 "Error, unexpected number\n" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 282 "When we have two equations in \+
two variables, we think of the solution set of this system of equation
s as being the set of points (x,y) which satisfy both equations simult
aneously.  In terms of their graphs, the solution set is the set of po
ints where the graphs intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 622 "When we have two linear equati
ons in two variables, since their graphs are straight lines, then two \+
straight lines, if they cross, will cross in exactly one place.  Hence
, the solution set of the system of equations will be exactly one poin
t (x,y).  If we have two equations which are more complicated, then th
e number of intersection points (crossing points) of their graphs can \+
vary.  For example, if the graph of one equation is a circle and the g
raph of the other equation is a straight line, then, if their graphs c
ross, then number of solutions (intersection points) of the system of \+
equations could be 1 or 2.  Etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 128 "We can instruct Maple to find solutions \+
of systems of equations using the solve or fsolve commands.  The synta
x for doing so is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 30 "     solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 85 "where eq1 and eq2 are eq
uations in the variables x and y.  This is illustrated below." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
42 "solve(\{ x + 2*y = 5, 2*x-3*y = -1\},\{x,y\});" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "We could have defined \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 40 "eq1 := x + 2*y = 5;\neq2 := \+
2*x-3*y = -1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&%\"xG\"\"\"
*&\"\"#F(%\"yGF(F(\"\"&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2G/,&*
&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*&\"\"$F)%\"yGF)!\"\"F." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 26 "and then given the comman
d" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\})
;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" 
}}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 55 "and ac
hieved the same result.  Remember the solution  (" }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "13/
7" "6#*&\"#8\"\"\"\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "11/7" "
6#*&\"#6\"\"\"\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 127 ") represents a point in the t
wo-dimensional plane (why two-dimensional?) where the graphs of the eq
uations intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 63 "Find the solutions, if they exist, for the foll
owing equations " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 4 "a.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x - 2*y = 6" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%
\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"'" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "
4*x + y = -2" "6#/,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'%\"yGF',$\"\"#!\"\"" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "eq1:=3*x-2*y = 6;" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*&\"\"#F)%\"
yGF)!\"\"\"\"'" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "eq2:=4*x+
y = -2;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2G/,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"x
GF)F)%\"yGF)!\"#" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "solve( \+
\{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"xG#\"
\"#\"#6/%\"yG#!#IF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
